\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. S. aquaticus} Hill, {\i Veg. Syst.}{\b  2}: 120 (17613. Like {\b 44} but more constantly biennial; stems often branched in lower part; basal leaves often undivided, more persistent at anthesis; corymb less dense; capitula 12-30 mm in diameter; achenes all glabrous or the inner with rather sparse hairs confined to the ribs. 2n = 40. {\i Wet places. S., W. & C. Europe, extending to S. Sweden and the western margin of the U.S.S.R.} All except Bl Cr Fa Fe Is Rs (N, C, K, E).
