\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. S. aethnensis} Jan ex DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  6}: 345 (1838). Subglabrous, glaucous perennial up to 40 cm, with erect stems from a branched, woody stock. Leaves fleshy, entire or dentate, the lowest oblanceolate-spathulate, more or less petiolate, the middle and upper cauline lanceolate, auriculate-amplexicaul. Capitula (20-)25-40 mm in diameter, few, in a terminal corymb. Involucral bracts c. 20, 8-10 mm, usually green; supplementary bracts several, 3-4 mm, often black-tipped. Ligules 8-12, c. 15 mm, bright yellow. Achenes (3-)3·5-4 mm, glabrous.{\i  Lava-slopes, mainly above} 1000{\i  m. •  Sicilia} ({\i Etna}). Si.
